text:
Depart from evil, and do good;
and dwell for evermore.
-Psalm 37 KJV

Thou shalt not be afraid 
for the terror by night; 
nor for the arrow that flieth by day;
-Psalm 91 KJV

His head and his hairs 
were white like wool, 
as white as snow; 
&amp; his eyes were as a flame of fire; 
-Book 0f Revelation 1:14 KJV

I will praise thee; 
for I am fearfully &amp; wonderfully made:
-Psalm 139 KJV

RT @Book0fPsaLm: 6 I will freely sacrifice unto thee: 
I will praise thy name, O LORD;
for it is good.

RT @power_peel_21: Retweeted THE HOLY BIBLE (@HolyBibLeKJB):

Have mercy upon me, O LORD; 
for I am weak: O LORD, heal me;
-Psalm 6 KJV

And said unto his servants,
This is John the Baptist;
he is risen from the dead;
and therefore mighty works
do shew forth themselves in him.

To day, after so long a time; 
as it is said, To day 
if ye will hear his voice, 
harden not your hearts. 
-Hebrews 4 KJV

6 O come, 
let us worship and bow down: 
let us kneel before the LORD our maker.

Bless the LORD, O my soul.
O LORD my God,
thou art very great;

he will have compassion upon us;
he will subdue our iniquities;
&amp; thou wilt cast all their sins
into the depths of the sea.
-Micah 7:19 KJV

We are fools for Christ's sake, 
but ye are wise in Christ; 
we are weak, but ye are strong; 
ye are honourable, 
but we are despised.

If he called them gods,
unto whom the word of God came,
and the scripture cannot be broken;

For a good work we stone thee not;
but for blasphemy; 
and because that thou, 
being a man, makest thyself God.

Have mercy upon me, O LORD; 
for I am weak: O LORD, heal me;
-Psalm 6 KJV

And John was clothed 
with camel's hair, &amp; with a girdle 
of a skin about his loins; 
&amp; he did eat locusts 
and wild honey;
-Mark 1:6 KJV

We have drunken our water for money;
our wood is sold unto us.
-Lamentations 5 KJV

In him was life;
and the life was the light of men.
-Book 0f John 1 KJV
